re’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":9,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":18,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir William of Carrington was born on 10 December 1205, in Carrington, Cheshire, England, his father, Sir Michael of Carrington, was 22 and his mother, Mrs. Michael of Carrington, was 24. He had at least 4 sons with Ciceley de Massey II. He died in 1241, in his hometown, at the age of 36."},"et":{"10 December 1205–1241":"10. detsember 1205–1241","1205–1241":"1205–1241","1208–1300":"1208–1300","1230–1274":"1230–1274","1232–Male":"1232–Surnud","1234–Male":"1234–Surnud","1236–1296":"1236–1296","1182–1241":"1182–1241","1182–Female":"1182–Surnud","10 December 1205":"10. detsember 1205","1230":"1230","1241":"1241","1296":"1296","1274":"1274","1182":"1182","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1236":"1236","1